title: The Brookline cockatoo is back in its cage - Massachusetts news
text:
The fugitive that’s spent the past three months terrorizing Brookline residents is finally back in his cage.
Dino, the recluse cockatoo who’s been gnawing holes in the home where Robert F. Kennedy was born and waking residents with his early morning screeching, was apprehended Thursday afternoon, The Boston Globe reported.
Dino fled from his cage in July, evading multiple capture attempts—allegedly with the help of one neighbor possibly seeking to sabotage the attempts, the Globe reported. On Thursday, a team of rescue workers combined efforts with some volunteers and a bird enthusiast to cage Dino, finally returning him to his rightful home.
